  "texts": [
    "Thus, we can describe the induced localized symmetries in the g-sector by a (non-fusion) (q -1)-categoryC (q-1) g (O q).",
    "(55)In total, all induced localized symmetries are described by a (q -1)-categoryC (q-1) (O q):= g∈G (0) C (q-1) g (O q).",
    "(56)The composition of induced localized symmetries lying in different sectors discussed in the previous paragraph becomes a fusion structure on the (q -1)-category C (q-1) (O q), converting it into a fusion (q -1)-category.",
    "Moreover, since the fusion respects the group multiplication of the underlying sectors C (q-1) (O q) is in fact a G (0) -graded fusion (q -1)-category.",
    "Now, G (0) -graded fusion (q -1)-categories describe only 1-dimensional (q + 1)representations."
